		<a name="85409"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/17/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 05:45:03</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=9215"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=9215')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=85409&amp;TOPIC_ID=9848&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Soloing+the+Plane+of+Growth&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         You can hunt most of the non-named mobs in PoG. Most of the mobs up there summon, but are easy to root and only summon every 12 seconds. Pull with snare, then root and cook, and move away when they summon.<BR>Not very good exp though, even after the exp patch, but you can make some really nice cash.<BR>Wait till you are level 60 though, and you better have at least 2k HPs unbuffed because you're gonna have to be able to take a beating. Ask a friendly cleric for some HP buff too. Having Aego, BMB and focus helps alot, and those buffs last a really long time.</P><P>My best advice would be to bring along a shaman though. Me and my shaman friend oftenly duo in PoG. With shaman slow, we can even take some of the named ones. The shaman, me, and my EoT-pet take turns getting hit, and we load a bunch of dots on the mobs, and it usualy turns out well :) We've been hunting there for a total of 20 hours I think, and neither of us has ever died. We had to gate out a few times, but never died. Necro pulls, and shaman slows ASAP! And if you get adds, just slow them and hope you don't get more :) We easily managed 3 mobs at once after a bad pull, and two of them were healers. (They don't complete heal though.)<BR>A hint though, try to let the necro have the highest agro. If things go wrong, the shaman will need a few extra seconds to gate out. Just let him gate out, and then you FD. Piece a cake!</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
